node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

node.text:
I’ve gained and lost weight throughout Covid. I know this not because I weigh myself — I don’t, I refuse to — but because I can see it in my body, feel it in my skin.

And that’s ok.

There’s was a time when these kind of changes would have sent me into a tailspin.

I viewed my WEIGHT as intrinsically tied to my WORTH.
And changes in it were measures of GOOD or BAD.
SUCCESS or FAILURE.

Today, now, I don’t play that game.
I don’t even let myself go there.

Instead, when I find my mind sliding into that dangerous space,
Of staring down flaws in the mirror or searching out fistfuls of squishy skin with my hands,
I pull back. I pause.
And I ask myself what is really bothering me.

Sometimes, yes, sometimes it’s my body.
Because that’s human and that’s conditioned.
But more often than that, it’s emotional.
Mental.
Maybe a lack of control in this or feeling not good enough in that.

And whatever the answer is,
I treat it gently.

Because self love isn’t about feeling shiny in your skin every single moment.
It’s knowing that who you ARE doesn’t CHANGE even if your body does.

So today, today I just wanted to remind you these things.
Especially now, as my inbox is full with so many messages on Covid and body image struggles.

I just wanted to stress how incredible you are.
How powerful. How strong.
And how even if your WEIGHT fluctuates,
Your WORTH does not.

I’m so glad you’re here.
I’m grateful we’re in this together.️⁣⁣️️️️️️️️️️️️

node.text:
Ladies you NEED to check out @SculptSwim for summers hottest bikinis 👙 

Do you want to get toned? Build lean muscle? ⁣
⁣
Well you’re going about it the wrong way⁣
⁣
These things will NOT get you toned:⁣
⁣
❌ lifting light weights⁣
⁣
❌ doing random exercises every week⁣
⁣
❌ doing a ton of cardio (you can actually burn off your muscle)⁣
⁣
❌ doing high reps and going for burn out⁣
⁣
INSTEAD try this⁣
⁣
✅ stick to structured workouts for 4 weeks minimum before changing them up⁣
⁣
…. Yes it sometimes gets boring⁣
⁣
✅ lift as heavy as you can with proper form and focus on trying to lift heavier each week⁣
⁣
…. No you won’t get bulky I promise⁣
⁣
✅ rep ranges 6-12 is for muscle hypertrophy (muscle growth)⁣
⁣
…… Reps 1-5 are for maximal strength and 12-20+ for muscle endurance (NASM)⁣
⁣
✅ eat adequate protein⁣
⁣
…….. aim for .8-1.1g per lb of lean body mass⁣
⁣
⁣
But most importantly BE PATIENT⁣
⁣
Building muscle and getting toned take time and consistency⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sculpt Lifestyle on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text.

node.text:
1.7 STONE DIFFERENCE (10.7kg up in 26 weeks)⁣

Visit @GymGlutes 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit!

⁣
Before I ramble on I just wanted to say thank you!! Thank you all for supporting my journey. I am so happy I can help so many of you on your journeys and to normalise weight gain♥️⁣
⁣
Measurements: ⁣
Height - 5 ft 10⁣
Waist - 30 inches⁣
Glutes - 43 inches⁣
Weight - in the picture☺️⁣
⁣
3800 calories ⁣
No cardio⁣
⁣
Another week ticked off and as you guys know it’s been harder these past few weeks with some negative comments BUT that’s what fuels me even more to my goals! ⁣
⁣
I’m around 17 weeks (4 months) away from starting prep for 2021 which is crazyyyy to think about but that’s 17 weeks to push myself harder in this bulk!⁣
⁣
2 weeks isolating has meant home training but I’m still working and adapting around the situation! I’ll be back in the gym next Thursday and I cannot wait😭 ⁣
⁣
Ready to smash another week💪🏻⁣
.
.
.
Credit: @gljfitnessuk #abworkout #coreworkout #quadsworkout #legworkout #gluteworkout #workoutvideos  #gymmotivation #bodybuilding #fitnessmotivation #homeworkout #fullbodyworkout #bodyweightworkout
